Abuja – The Federal Capital Territory Administration (FCTA) has put plans in place to make education more accessible to residents through its e-education platforms in its schools across the territory. Education Secretary, Hon. Sani Dahir El-Katuzu, gave said this during the FCT Administration’s Executive Committee meeting, held on Monday, June 27, 2022 and chaired by the FCT Minister, Muhammad Musa Bello. El-Katuzu said this plan was a part of the Education Secretariat’s presentation to the Executive Committee. According to him in a statement made available to newsmen by the Chief Press Secretary to the FCT Minister, Mr Anthony Ogunlelye, stated that, when fully operational, this measure would enable students who are unable to attend classes physically attend virtually while results could be accessed and students’ performance monitored online amongst other services.